Announcements

Jan 2022

01 Oct

Congratulations to Germaine Loi (4EL) for being the SSSC Best Sportsgirl for Taekwondo 2021. 


Germaine won 1st placing in both Black Belt 1 individual and team events in the National Schools Game TKD championship this year. Germaine and many other Edgefield TKD representatives contributed to our school clincing the B Division Girls Championship title this year. Our B Division Boys attained 2nd placing in the Boys Championship. Well-done to Edgefield Boys and Girls team. 


Germaine has been a member of the Singapore Taekwondo Federation’s (STF) high development squad since end-2018. She has represented Singapore in many international competitions as part of the STF’s high development squad.

 

Germaine demonstrates empathy and team spirit, often showing care and offering encouragement especially towards newcomers in the high development squad. She will take time to explain the required Taekwondo training to newcomers who were not familiar with them.


Once again, we are happy and proud of Germaine's achievement as the Best Sportsgirl for Taekwondo 2021.  


Read more about her in this Straits Time article - https://www.straitstimes.com/sport/schools/school-sports-1300-student-athletes-earn-kudos-at-colours-awards
